# ─── .dockerignore — keep Docker build context lean & deterministic ──────
#
# Without this, every COPY step's cache key includes the entire repo
# (node_modules, .git, the pdf-service subdir, screenshots, etc).
# A change in any of those invalidates Buildkit cache layers
# unrelated to the main-app build, and on Railway it has shown up as
# "failed to compute cache key: ... not found" errors that are really
# just stale-cache symptoms.
#
# Anything not listed here is included. Keep this list tight — adding
# too much can break the build (the Next.js app needs prisma/, public/,
# src/, etc.).

node_modules
.next
.git
.github
.vscode
.cursor
.idea
.DS_Store

# Local env + secrets — never bake into the image.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# pdf-service is a separate Railway service with its own Dockerfile.
# Excluding it from the main app's build context keeps cache keys
# stable (a tweak to pdf-service/index.js shouldn't invalidate a
# Next.js layer).
pdf-service

# Local artefacts that don't belong in the image
coverage
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# Tooling output the build doesn't need
storybook-static
playwright-report
test-results
